The paper deals with coding theory and information theory, specifically the design of codes that achieve capacity on the binary erasure channel with bounded complexity. This falls under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of ensembles of codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). The use of computer simulations to compare the performance of different codes suggests a focus on networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) or systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the paper introduces symmetry properties which could be related to the study of symmetry in computer science (cs.DS).
